"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The roc_auc_score function in scikit-learn expects the true labels to be binary (0 or 1) or -1 for negative and 1 for positive, but it also expects both classes to be present in the labels. In this case, the true labels are all 1, which means there is only one class present. This will raise a ValueError.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5,6\\n<predicted_scores = np.array([0.9, 0.8, 0.4])\\n---\\n>true_labels = np.array([1, 0, 1])\\n>predicted_scores = np.array([0.9, 0.8, 0.4])\"\n}"